Hoodlums have reportedly attacked the residence of Plateau Governor Simon Lalong’s father-in law’s house at Tudan Wada, Jos. The Nation learnt though the father-in-law was not harmed valuables were carted away from the residence. It was gathered security agents were immediately deployed to disperse the hoodlums. The School of Home Economy, the Local Government Secretariat in Riyom, the warehouse as well as the NSCDC Office were reportedly vandalised.
